## Admin Web App screens and flow

## 1) Splash / Boot

**Why:** decide where to route (login vs dashboard) and hydrate auth state.
**Does:** reads token from storage, sets auth headers globally.
**APIs:** none.

---

## 2) Login

**Why:** Admin entry point.
**Does:** email/password login, store token, route to dashboard.
**API:** `POST /auth/login`
**Output used:** `accessToken`, `user.role` (must be ADMIN).

---

## 3) Admin Dashboard (Home)

**Why:** admin needs тАЬwhatтАЩs happening right nowтАЭ in one place.
**Does:** shows totals + trends + pending review stats, quick links.
**APIs:** (all or subset depending on widgets)

* `GET /dashboard/summary`
* `GET /dashboard/recent-submissions`
* `GET /dashboard/trends`
* `GET /dashboard/pending-aging`
* `GET /dashboard/top-submitters`
* `GET /dashboard/plant-summary`
* `GET /dashboard/template-summary`

---

## 4) Plants Management

**Why:** everything is plant-scoped (forms, users, submissions).
**Does:** list plants + create plant.
**APIs:**

* `GET /plants`
* `POST /plants` (payload `{ name }`)

---

## 5) Users Management

**Why:** admin controls who can access what (managers/users + plant assignments).
**Does:** list/search users, create managers, edit users, enable/disable users.
**APIs:**

* `GET /users` (filters: q, role, plantId, active, page, limit)
* `POST /users/managers` (create manager with plantIds)
* `PATCH /users/{id}` (edit name/email/role/plantIds/active)
* `PATCH /users/{id}/enable`
* `PATCH /users/{id}/disable`

**UX note:** тАЬCreate USERтАЭ is managerтАЩs job via `/users/plants/{plantId}/users`, but admin UI can still show it as read-only or add it later if you want.

---

## 6) Forms Templates (Library/List)

**Why:** admin needs a place to manage all templates + their lifecycle.
**Does:** list templates with filters (status, search), show versioning, actions.
**APIs:**

* `GET /forms` (q/status/page/limit)

**Actions from list:**

* Open details: `GET /forms/{id}`
* Clone: `POST /forms/{id}/clone`
* Archive: `POST /forms/{id}/archive` (only published)

---

## 7) Template Detail / Editor (DRAFT only)

**Why:** to create/edit a template safely before publishing.
**Does:** form builder UI for fields; edit title/plantIds; field ordering; dropdown options.
**APIs:**

* Load: `GET /forms/{id}`
* Save: `PATCH /forms/{id}` (only DRAFT)
* Publish: `POST /forms/{id}/publish` (only DRAFT + must have fields)

**Important lifecycle rules enforced by backend:**

* Published templates cannot be edited
* Archive only published templates

---

## 8) Template Import Screen

**Why:** faster creation from Excel тЖТ JSON (your Option A import flow).
**Does:** upload Excel тЖТ frontend converts тЖТ preview fields тЖТ send JSON to backend to create DRAFT.
**API:**

* `POST /forms/import` (payload: title, plantIds, fields[])

Then admin goes to Template Editor screen to review and publish.

---

## 9) Submissions Review (Admin Review Queue)

**Why:** admin must monitor/override review process (and can review too).
**Does:** list submissions, filter by plant/status/search, open details.
**APIs:**

* `GET /mobile/forms/submissions` (admin can see all; supports paging/search/status)

---

## 10) Submission Detail (Review + Evidence)

**Why:** approve/reject decisions need full context: answers + fields + photos + reject reason.
**Does:** view enriched submission; open photos; approve/reject with reason.
**APIs:**

* `GET /mobile/forms/submissions/{id}`
* Photos: `GET /files/signed-url?key=photos/...`
* Approve: `POST /mobile/forms/submissions/{id}/approve`
* Reject: `POST /mobile/forms/submissions/{id}/reject` with `{ reason }`

---

## 11) Reports / Analytics (Optional separate screen)

**Why:** dashboards often grow; you may separate dashboards into a тАЬReportsтАЭ section.
**Does:** plant summary, template summary, trends charts, top submitters table.
**APIs:**

* all `/dashboard/*`

---

## 12) System Status (Optional)

**Why:** quick debug to know if DB/MinIO is alive.
**Does:** show `/health` results + version info.
**API:** `GET /health`

